WEBVTT

00:36.493 --> 00:39.462
These are the true events
of November, 1965.

00:40.497 --> 00:42.465
The la Drang Valley
of Vietnam.

00:43.500 --> 00:46.469
A place our country does
not remember...

00:46.570 --> 00:48.470
...in a war it does
not understand.

00:49.506 --> 00:51.474
This story is the testament
to the young...

00:51.575 --> 00:53.475
...Americans who died in the
Valley of Death...

00:53.577 --> 00:55.306
...and a tribute
to the young men...

00:55.412 --> 00:57.141
...of the People's Army
of Vietnam...

00:57.248 --> 00:58.840
...who died by our hand
in that place.

01:01.452 --> 01:03.420
To tell this story, l must start...

01:03.520 --> 01:04.418
...at the beginning.

01:06.457 --> 01:08.425
But where does it begin?

01:11.462 --> 01:12.895
Maybe in June of 1954...

01:12.997 --> 01:15.431
...when French Group Mobile
1 00 moved into...

01:15.532 --> 01:17.432
...the same Central Highlands
of Vietnam...

01:17.534 --> 01:20.435
...where we would go
1 1 years later.

01:34.485 --> 01:35.452
See anything?

01:37.488 --> 01:39.456
No, Captain.

01:39.556 --> 01:41.456
Fucking grass...

01:41.558 --> 01:43.458
Fucking heat...

01:44.495 --> 01:45.462
Fucking country...

03:18.455 --> 03:20.423
Do we take prisoners?

03:21.458 --> 03:24.427
No. Kill all they send...

03:24.528 --> 03:26.428
...and they will stop coming.

04:17.447 --> 04:20.416
Maybe the story begins
in America...

04:20.517 --> 04:22.417
...when the Army
first realized...

04:22.519 --> 04:24.419
...a new kind of war was
coming its way.

04:24.521 --> 04:26.421
The White House anticipates
a buildup...

04:26.523 --> 04:27.751
...and wants a victory.

04:27.858 --> 04:29.416
Over cavemen,
in black pajamas.

04:29.526 --> 04:32.051
We wouldn't be there if they
hadn't already beaten...

04:32.162 --> 04:33.094
...the French Army.

04:33.197 --> 04:35.427
The French Army?
What's that?

04:35.532 --> 04:37.432
The problem in Vietnam
is terrain.

04:37.534 --> 04:39.832
Jungle, mountains, rivers,
maneuver is a nightmare.

04:39.937 --> 04:42.405
That's why we came up with
the plan to use helicopters.

04:42.506 --> 04:43.438
Leap in and out of battle.

04:43.540 --> 04:45.440
They want you to run
the test on the idea.

04:45.542 --> 04:47.442
lt'll take a hell
of a combat leader.

04:47.544 --> 04:50.445
l know a young light Colonel
named Hal Moore.

04:50.547 --> 04:53.448
He led a combat company
in Korea.

04:53.550 --> 04:56.451
After that he volunteered
to test experimental parachutes.

04:56.553 --> 04:59.454
Experimental parachutes?
Sounds like just the guy.

04:59.556 --> 05:01.387
The other side
of the mountain...

05:01.492 --> 05:03.392
...was all that he can see.

05:03.494 --> 05:05.394
Was all that he can see...

05:05.496 --> 05:07.396
...was all that he can see.

05:07.498 --> 05:10.399
The other side
of the mountain...

05:10.501 --> 05:12.401
...was all that he can see.

05:12.503 --> 05:14.403
The bear went over
the mountain...

05:14.505 --> 05:16.405
...the bear went over
the mountain...

05:16.507 --> 05:17.838
...the bear went over
the mountain...

05:17.941 --> 05:19.408
How about we go back
to Bingo?

05:19.510 --> 05:21.410
-What do you say? Bingo!
-Oh...

05:23.447 --> 05:26.416
B-l-N-G-O...
B-l-N-G-O...

05:48.472 --> 05:49.439
Tom...

05:50.474 --> 05:52.408
How much you know about
our new Colonel?

05:52.509 --> 05:53.441
He was in Korea.

05:53.544 --> 05:56.445
Has a Masters in lnternational
Relations from Harvard.

05:56.547 --> 05:59.448
Harvard? He's not one of those
academic pussies, is he?

05:59.550 --> 06:01.381
Hal Moore?

06:35.452 --> 06:37.420
