06:54.471 --> 06:57.440
Come on, Too Tall,
give me you best shot, baby!

06:59.476 --> 07:00.443
Did you see that?

07:01.411 --> 07:03.379
Did you see that?

07:03.480 --> 07:06.381
Snakeshit drives that
one to the moon.

07:06.483 --> 07:07.381
To the moon!

07:08.418 --> 07:09.385
And he's coming around...

07:11.421 --> 07:13.389
No, he's not...

07:17.427 --> 07:20.396
You're out, Snakeshit!
You're out!

07:20.497 --> 07:23.398
Horseshit! No wonder you
can't fly! You can't see!

07:25.435 --> 07:26.402
l believe you're out.

07:34.444 --> 07:37.413
-You're a pilot?
-Too Tall, sir.

07:37.514 --> 07:40.415
-Yeah, l can see that.
-You call, we haul.

07:42.452 --> 07:45.421
-Can l speak to you a minute?
-Yes, sir.

07:45.522 --> 07:47.422
-Out!
-Safe.

07:50.460 --> 07:52.428
-Can l buy you a drink?
-Sure.

07:53.463 --> 07:54.430
Oh, thanks.

07:55.465 --> 07:58.059
So your men
call you, Snakeshit?

07:58.168 --> 07:59.897
That's an affectionate
appellation...

08:00.003 --> 08:01.368
...of my comrades-in-arms, sir.

08:01.471 --> 08:03.371
Because l fly lower
than snakeshit.

08:03.473 --> 08:05.373
Well, l gotta problem,
Snakeshit.

08:05.475 --> 08:07.375
And l think you're the solution.

08:07.477 --> 08:10.378
l've been called a lot of
things, Colonel never a solution.

08:10.480 --> 08:12.380
You know what Air Cavalry
really means?

08:12.482 --> 08:15.178
You fly into hostile territory,
out-numbered.

08:15.285 --> 08:17.116
1 0,000 miles from home.

08:17.220 --> 08:20.383
Sometimes the battleground's
no bigger than a football field.

08:20.490 --> 08:23.391
And if the choppers stop
coming we all get slaughtered.

08:24.428 --> 08:26.396
Now l figure, chopper pilots
won't fly...

08:26.496 --> 08:27.861
...into hell for strangers so...

08:27.964 --> 08:30.398
-...l'm Hal Moore.
-l know, sir.

08:30.500 --> 08:32.400
Why us?

08:32.501 --> 08:35.403
Well, you guys look like shit.

08:35.505 --> 08:37.405
But your equipment
is immaculate.

08:37.506 --> 08:39.566
Yesterday was Sunday, you
didn't have to be...

08:39.676 --> 08:40.700
...training but you were.

08:40.811 --> 08:43.405
And you got pilots like that
Too Tall character.

08:43.513 --> 08:46.414
He's way outside the limits
of Army regs...

08:46.516 --> 08:49.041
...they want to fly with
you for some reason.

08:49.152 --> 08:51.746
l guess it's because
they think you're the best.

08:51.855 --> 08:54.415
lt's because l only recruit
the dumb ones, sir.

08:57.461 --> 09:00.430
l suppose that l have a choice
in all of this.

09:00.530 --> 09:01.360
You sure don't.

09:02.399 --> 09:05.368
l wouldn't miss it for
the world.

09:05.469 --> 09:07.369
To The Air Cav.

09:15.412 --> 09:17.039
Good morning, Sergeant-Major.

09:17.147 --> 09:19.741
How do you know what kind
of goddamn day it is?

09:27.424 --> 09:28.391
Group!

09:29.426 --> 09:31.394
Attention!

09:55.452 --> 09:57.420
At ease, Gentlemen!

09:59.456 --> 10:01.424
Welcome to the new cavalry.

10:02.459 --> 10:04.427
We will ride into battle.

10:05.462 --> 10:06.429
And this...

10:07.464 --> 10:09.432
...will be our horse.

10:33.490 --> 10:35.458
You don't have to catch it.

10:36.493 --> 10:38.461
You don't have to feed it.

10:38.562 --> 10:40.462
But l can assure you...

10:41.498 --> 10:43.466
...that neither
the new technology...

10:44.501 --> 10:46.469
...nor your status
as officers...

10:46.570 --> 10:49.471
...will keep you above
the danger.

10:50.507 --> 10:53.476
Sergeant-Major Plumley and
l come from the paratroopers...

10:53.577 --> 10:56.478
...where the officer is always
the first one out of the plane...

10:57.514 --> 11:00.483
...because to follow
your instincts...

11:00.584 --> 11:03.417
...and to inspire your men
by your example...

11:03.520 --> 11:05.420
...you have to be with them...

11:05.522 --> 11:08.423
...where the metal meets
the meat.

11:09.459 --> 11:12.428
Sergeant- Major Plumley made
all 4 combat jumps...

11:12.529 --> 11:15.430
...in the 82nd Airborne during
World War ll.

11:15.532 --> 11:18.433
Sicily, Salerno, Normandy
and Holland...

11:18.535 --> 11:20.435
...plus one more in Korea.

11:22.472 --> 11:24.440
He answers to me...

11:24.541 --> 11:25.439
...and to me alone.

11:26.476 --> 11:29.445
Now l hope you Gentlemen
like training.

11:29.546 --> 11:31.446
Because me and the
Sergeant-Major...

11:32.482 --> 11:33.449
...we love it.

11:36.486 --> 11:39.455
Three strikes
and you're not out!

11:39.556 --> 11:42.457
There is always one more
thing you can do!

11:55.505 --> 11:57.473
Go! Go! Now!

11:58.508 --> 11:59.475
-2...
-Let's go!

12:00.510 --> 12:01.408
...3.

12:04.447 --> 12:06.415
-Pretty good, no?
-Pretty good.

12:08.451 --> 12:10.419
There's only one thing wrong.

12:10.954 --> 12:13.013
Let's be sharp, men!
We will be the best...

12:13.123 --> 12:14.420
...platoon in this battalion.

12:15.458 --> 12:18.427
Be ready in there!
Let's go! Let's go!

12:18.528 --> 12:21.429
Alright! Your officer's dead!
What do you do?

12:21.531 --> 12:22.429
What do you do?

12:23.466 --> 12:26.435
Alright, he hesitated! He's dead!
What do you do?

12:26.536 --> 12:29.437
-Get off the chopper!
-Get off the chopper!

12:36.479 --> 12:38.447
Alright, all officers.

12:38.548 --> 12:39.446
Come on in.

12:41.484 --> 12:44.453
Savage, you learn the job
of the man above you.

12:44.554 --> 12:47.455
And you teach your job
to the man below you in rank.

12:47.557 --> 12:50.458
That goes for every man
in this outfit. Understood?

12:50.560 --> 12:53.461
Yes, Sir!
We'll be landing under fire.

12:56.499 --> 12:58.467
Men will die.

13:05.241 --> 13:06.674
Have you said your prayers?

13:06.776 --> 13:07.401
No?

13:08.445 --> 13:10.413
-No.
-l'll say them with you.

13:11.448 --> 13:13.416
Fall in.

13:16.453 --> 13:19.422
Alright.
Ready? Set.

13:19.522 --> 13:21.114
ln the name of The Father,
The Son...

13:21.224 --> 13:22.418
...and The Holy Ghost.
Amen.

13:22.525 --> 13:25.426
Hail Mary, full of grace...

13:25.528 --> 13:28.429
...the Lord is with thee. Blessed
art thou amongst women...

13:28.531 --> 13:31.432
...and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb...

13:31.534 --> 13:32.728
Holy Mary, mother of...

13:32.836 --> 13:34.895
Cecile, l don't hear you
praying, honey.

13:36.473 --> 13:37.906
l don't want to be a Catholic.

13:38.008 --> 13:39.771
l want to be a Methodist
like Mommy.

13:39.876 --> 13:40.433
You do?

13:42.479 --> 13:44.447
And why is that, honey?

13:44.547 --> 13:46.447
So l can pray whatever
l want.

13:47.484 --> 13:50.453
-That's a sin.
-No, no, that's not a sin.

13:50.553 --> 13:53.454
God just made you hardheaded.
That's not a sin.

13:54.491 --> 13:56.459
l'll tell you what,
do you want to...

13:56.559 --> 13:59.460
...do you want to pray and thank
God for our family?

14:00.497 --> 14:03.398
-Yes, sir.
-That's good, then let's do it.

14:04.434 --> 14:07.403
Hail Mary, full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

14:07.504 --> 14:10.405
Blessed art thou
among women...

14:10.507 --> 14:12.407
...and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

14:17.080 --> 14:19.640
l can hear you laughing,
you know, even in here.

14:20.450 --> 14:22.418
l'm not laughing, l'm marveling.

14:23.453 --> 14:25.421
Marveling? About what?

14:25.522 --> 14:27.046
That you can find
stubbornness...

14:27.157 --> 14:29.091
...in your children and
think it comes...

14:29.192 --> 14:30.420
...from anybody but you.

14:30.527 --> 14:31.425
Oh, yeah?

14:35.465 --> 14:38.434
l'll give you something
to marvel at.

15:00.490 --> 15:01.388
When l pray...

15:03.426 --> 15:05.394
...whatever l want...

15:06.429 --> 15:08.397
l thank God for you.

15:22.445 --> 15:24.413
lt's a beautiful morning,
Sergeant-Major.

15:24.514 --> 15:27.415
Are you a fuckin'
weatherman now?

15:30.453 --> 15:33.422
Look what l found for the
new baseball player.

15:33.523 --> 15:35.423
They've sent us another
bunch of officers.

15:35.525 --> 15:38.426
Real green.
Got to train them up.

15:38.528 --> 15:41.429
Makes me think of starting
a new unit.

15:41.531 --> 15:43.431
They sent new rifles too.
The M-1 6.

15:43.533 --> 15:45.433
lt's supposed to be a
pretty good weapon.

15:45.535 --> 15:47.435
Ah, lots of plastic.

15:47.537 --> 15:49.437
Feels like a B-B gun to me.

15:49.539 --> 15:51.439
l think l'll stick
with my pistol.

15:51.541 --> 15:53.441
You think we're going to get
close enough...

15:53.543 --> 15:55.010
...to the enemy to use that?

15:55.111 --> 15:56.442
What do you think, sir?

15:57.480 --> 16:00.449
A leader must remain
cool and calm.

16:00.550 --> 16:02.381
And second you must
learn to ignore...

16:02.485 --> 16:05.386
...the explosions,
the heat, the dust...

16:05.488 --> 16:07.388
...the screams of the wounded.

16:07.490 --> 16:10.391
This is normal on the battlefield.
Normal.

16:22.438 --> 16:24.406
...l got wounded...

16:24.507 --> 16:26.338
Sir, we need the helicopters
over with...

16:26.442 --> 16:27.670
...reinforcements right now...

16:28.444 --> 16:30.412
Where the hell is
that coming from?

16:30.513 --> 16:32.413
lt's our advisors in Vietnam.

16:32.515 --> 16:35.416
The new radio's picking up
atmospheric bounce.

16:52.468 --> 16:55.437
When Crazy Horse
was a baby...

16:59.475 --> 17:02.376
...he nursed from the breast
of every woman in the tribe.

17:04.414 --> 17:07.383
The Sioux raised their
children that way.

17:08.417 --> 17:10.386
Every warrior...

17:10.486 --> 17:13.387
...called every woman
in the tribe ''Mother''.

17:13.489 --> 17:16.390
Every older warrior they called
him ''Grandfather''.

17:16.492 --> 17:19.393
And the point here is they
fought as a family.

17:21.431 --> 17:23.398
Take care of your men.

17:23.499 --> 17:26.400
Teach them to take care
of each other.

17:27.436 --> 17:29.405
Because when this starts...

17:31.441 --> 17:34.410
...each other is all
we're going to have.

17:39.449 --> 17:42.418
-Did you tune that in?
-Yes, sir.

17:42.518 --> 17:45.419
That's fine.
You're my radio operator.

17:45.521 --> 17:46.920
-l...
-You'll be fine.

17:47.023 --> 17:48.422
You'll work it out.

17:55.465 --> 17:58.434
Any of you, son-of-a-bitches
calls me Grandpa...

18:00.470 --> 18:02.370
l'll kill you.

18:25.428 --> 18:27.396
Godboldt, take your boots off.

18:29.432 --> 18:30.399
Go on.

18:32.435 --> 18:34.403
Everybody, take your boots off.

18:34.504 --> 18:37.405
Everybody. Socks too.

18:52.121 --> 18:54.419
l want you to draw out fresh
socks from supply...

18:54.524 --> 18:57.425
...and keep your feet
dusted with powder.

19:00.463 --> 19:03.364
Everybody check each other's
feet like Godboldt and me.

19:05.401 --> 19:07.369
Now that young man's a leader.

19:07.470 --> 19:08.368
Yes, sir.

19:09.405 --> 19:11.373
But that other fellow...

19:11.474 --> 19:13.374
...that big strong one there...

19:13.476 --> 19:15.376
...he wants to win medals.

19:23.419 --> 19:25.387
He's eager.

19:27.423 --> 19:28.515
Ladies, l'm just
really glad...

19:29.492 --> 19:31.392
...that you're all
here today.

19:31.494 --> 19:34.088
l know that some of you are
new to the Army, and...

19:34.197 --> 19:35.892
...all of us are new
to this post...

19:35.998 --> 19:38.592
...so l thought we could
pull our resources and cover...

19:38.701 --> 19:40.396
...whatever questions
we might have.

19:40.503 --> 19:42.767
So why don't we start with
item number one:

19:42.872 --> 19:43.395
...food.

19:44.240 --> 19:45.867
lf the commissary is out of
something...

19:45.975 --> 19:47.408
...where's the best
place to shop?

19:48.444 --> 19:51.038
l tried Big Star, it's okay.

19:51.147 --> 19:53.206
But l keep thinking
my water is going to break...

19:53.316 --> 19:54.408
...right in the checkout aisle.

19:57.453 --> 19:59.421
So, that takes care
of food shopping.

19:59.522 --> 20:01.422
So, item number two:
laundry.

20:01.524 --> 20:03.515
The base washing machines
don't work.

20:03.626 --> 20:05.890
They're full of sand from
the swamp missions.

20:05.995 --> 20:09.055
-Alright, l'll take care of that.
-l've already complained.

20:09.165 --> 20:11.429
Well, we'll just go to
the General.

20:11.534 --> 20:14.435
ln the meantime, the
Laundromat in town is okay.

20:14.537 --> 20:17.438
They won't let you wash colored
things in their machines.

20:17.540 --> 20:18.905
At a public Laundromat?

20:19.008 --> 20:21.533
But l'm telling you they have
a big sign right...

20:21.644 --> 20:23.441
...in the window says,
''Whites Only''.

20:26.482 --> 20:28.450
-What?
-Honey, they mean...

20:28.551 --> 20:30.451
...white people only.

20:32.488 --> 20:34.456
That's awful.

20:34.557 --> 20:37.458
Your husband is wearing
the uniform of a country...

20:37.560 --> 20:40.461
...that allows a place to say
that his laundry's not good...

20:40.563 --> 20:43.464
...enough when
he could die for?

20:47.503 --> 20:50.472
-l'm sorry, l just...
-That's alright, honey.

20:50.573 --> 20:52.598
l know what my husband
is fighting for and...

20:52.708 --> 20:53.936
...that's why l can smile.

20:54.510 --> 20:57.479
My husband would never
ask for respect.

20:57.580 --> 21:00.481
And he'll give respect to no
man who hasn't earned it.

21:00.583 --> 21:02.414
The rest of his family is
the same way.

21:02.518 --> 21:05.419
And anybody who doesn't
respect that can keep...

21:05.521 --> 21:07.045
...his goddamn
washing machine...

21:07.156 --> 21:09.716
...because my baby's clothes
are going to be clean anyway.

21:10.460 --> 21:13.429
Well, l guess that takes care
of item number two.

21:17.467 --> 21:18.434
Are you alright?

21:19.469 --> 21:22.438
l think... l think my water
just broke.

21:22.538 --> 21:25.439
Okay, we're all calm.
We're all calm.

21:26.476 --> 21:29.445
The car!
l'll get the car!

22:02.445 --> 22:04.413
-Colonel.
-At ease. At ease.

22:04.514 --> 22:06.277
l heard one of my new
Lieutenant's...

22:06.382 --> 22:07.406
...just became a father.

22:07.517 --> 22:09.041
l came to say congratulations.

22:09.151 --> 22:11.415
-Thank you, sir.
-l didn't want to disturb you...

22:11.521 --> 22:14.422
No, no, it's fine.
lt's alright. Please.

22:15.458 --> 22:17.426
-How's your wife?
-She's okay.

22:17.527 --> 22:19.427
She's okay. She's sleeping.

22:19.529 --> 22:21.429
So is my daughter.

22:21.531 --> 22:23.431
l just wanted to be here
for a while...

22:23.533 --> 22:25.433
...before l held her.

22:26.469 --> 22:28.733
Did you tag her already?
What does that say?

22:28.838 --> 22:29.429
Oh, Camille.

22:29.539 --> 22:31.439
-l'm sorry, sir.
-No, don't you take that off.

22:31.541 --> 22:33.736
You leave that on where
it is. That's an order.

22:34.477 --> 22:37.446
Colonel, may
l ask you a question?

22:37.547 --> 22:38.445
Sure.

22:40.483 --> 22:42.451
What do you think about
being a...

22:42.552 --> 22:44.452
...soldier and a father?

22:45.488 --> 22:47.854
l hope that being good at
the one makes me...

22:47.957 --> 22:49.447
...better at the other.

22:52.495 --> 22:54.463
Why?
What about you?

22:55.498 --> 22:57.466
l don't know, sir.

22:57.567 --> 23:00.468
Between college and here...

23:00.570 --> 23:03.403
Barbara and l spent
a year in Africa.

23:04.440 --> 23:07.409
We helped build a school
for orphans.

23:09.445 --> 23:12.414
They were orphans because
the War Lord across...

23:12.515 --> 23:15.416
...the border didn't like
their tribe.

23:17.453 --> 23:21.412
l know God has a plan for me.

23:22.458 --> 23:25.586
l just hope it's to help
protect orphans...

23:26.462 --> 23:28.430
...not make any.

23:32.468 --> 23:34.436
Why don't we ask him?

23:35.471 --> 23:37.439
